  "prompt": "What happens when a batsman hit a shot and ball hits the spidercam?",
  "response": "When a batsman hits a shot and the ball strikes the Spidercam, the standard practice in cricket is to consider the ball dead. This means that the delivery does not count, and no runs are scored or dismissed as a result of the ball hitting the Spidercam. The delivery must be bowled again, and play resumes from the point before the ball was bowled. This is done to ensure fairness, as the ball hitting the Spidercam can alter its trajectory and impact the play in unpredictable ways.",
